On World Freedom Day, President Joseph R. Biden Jr. emphasizes the importance of the people's fight for freedom and democracy. He acknowledges the global resurgence of autocracy and highlights Russia's aggression against Ukraine as an example. The United States, along with its partners and allies, is committed to defending fundamental freedoms and human rights worldwide. The administration aims to create a future where equality and inclusion are upheld for all individuals, regardless of gender, race, ethnicity, or sexual orientation. President Biden also emphasizes the need to protect democracy within the United States itself. He commemorates the fall of the Berlin Wall as a symbol of hope and calls upon the American people to reaffirm their dedication to freedom and democracy. As President, he proclaims November 9, 2023, as World Freedom Day.